			<title>MADHU PANDIT DAS AND TEAM - The best animated movie: Little Krishna</title>
			<link>http://www.audarya-award.org/page/movie/9-madhu-pandit-das-and-team-the-best-animated-movie-little-krishna</link>
			<guid>http://www.audarya-award.org/page/movie/9-madhu-pandit-das-and-team-the-best-animated-movie-little-krishna</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<div style="text-align: center;">"Little Krishna" is the last and wonderful production by Akshaya Patra and Big Animation Studios.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<div style="text-align: center;"><strong>Synopsis of the movie:</strong></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">The  13 episodes of "Little Krishna" is  a result of seven years of  painstaking research work, handpicked from  the chronicles of Krishna,  the most remarkable stories of the legendary  prankstar in the Indian  heritage. The episodes are narrated in a  manner, engrossing enough to  mesmerize the audience world over, and  leave them spell-bound.</div>
</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">{youtube}sR5gGC5W_A4{/youtube}</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">

<img src="http://www.audarya-award.org/page/images/stories/photos/little_krishna/lk7.jpg" alt="" width="400" /></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://www.audarya-award.org/page/images/stories/photos/little_krishna/lk5.jpg" alt="" width="400" /></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">Little Krishna is the darling of Vrindavan, the land of peace and  tranquility, which is constantly threatened by the malice of evil king  Kamsa.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://www.audarya-award.org/page/images/stories/photos/little_krishna/lt3.jpg" alt="" /></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">While Krishna is busy with his endless pranks and mischiefs accompanied   by his friends, Kamsa remains restless for he is aware that Krishna is   his nemesis.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://www.audarya-award.org/page/images/stories/photos/little_krishna/lk4.jpg" alt="" width="400" /></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">As in the past, a prophecy had threatened Kamsa that his evil reign is  over, and a savior will descend on earth to make Kamsa meet his worst  adversity in life, which is his death. The only objective of Kamsa's  life therefore, was to find his angel of death.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://www.audarya-award.org/page/images/stories/photos/little_krishna/lk2.jpg" alt="" width="400" /></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">Congratulations to Madhu Pandit Dasa, chairman of the Akshaya Patra Foundation, and his team for this beatiful production.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://www.audarya-award.org/page/images/stories/photos/little_krishna/lk8.jpg" alt="" /></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://www.audarya-award.org/page/images/stories/photos/little_krishna/lk1.jpg" alt="" /></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">Chanchalapati Dasa, Vice Chairman of Akshaya Patra, received the  distinguished Audarya Award in the ‘Best animated movie’ category on  December 2010 at Akshaya Patra Vrindavan center.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://www.audarya-award.org/page/images/stories/photos/little_krishna/img_4918 720x480.jpg" alt="" width="400" /></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">The Goura Nitay trophy was given by Sripad Priyananda Bon Maharaj  representative of the Visva Vaishnava Raj Sabha (World Vaisnava  Association) with the presence of various local leaders and members of  the sabha.</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://www.audarya-award.org/page/images/stories/photos/little_krishna/img_4921 720x480.jpg" alt="" /></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">Chanchalapati Dasa</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://www.audarya-award.org/page/images/stories/photos/little_krishna/vrindavan 05.jpg" alt="" width="400" /></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">Akshaya Patra Mandir in Vrindavan</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://www.audarya-award.org/page/images/stories/photos/little_krishna/img_4955 720x480.jpg" alt="" width="400" /></div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;Sri Sri Radha Vrindavan Chandra</div>
